label.value: female meiotic nuclear division

value.value: A cell cycle process by which the cell nucleus divides as part of a meiotic cell cycle in the female germline.

definition.value: Note that female germ lines can be found in female or hermaphroditic organisms, so this term can be used to annotate gene products from hermaphrodites such as those of C. elegans. See also the biological process term 'meiotic nuclear division; GO:0140013'.

label.value: female meiosis I

value.value: The cell cycle process in which the first meiotic division occurs in the female germline.

label.value: meiotic recombination nodule assembly

value.value: During meiosis, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of strand exchange proteins (recombinases) to form small, electron dense structures in association with meiotic chromosomes.

label.value: female meiosis II

value.value: The cell cycle process in which the second meiotic division occurs in the female germline.

label.value: cell communication

value.value: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix, via cell adhesion molecules.

label.value: homophilic cell adhesion via plasma membrane adhesion molecules

value.value: The attachment of a plasma membrane adhesion molecule in one cell to an identical molecule in an adjacent cell.

label.value: heterophilic cell-cell adhesion via plasma membrane cell adhesion molecules

value.value: The attachment of an adhesion molecule in one cell to a nonidentical adhesion molecule in an adjacent cell.

label.value: neuron cell-cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of a neuron to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label.value: leukocyte cell-cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of a leukocyte to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label.value: cell-matrix adhesion

value.value: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules.

label.value: calcium-independent cell-matrix adhesion

value.value: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules that do not require the presence of calcium for the interaction.

label.value: negative regulation of cell adhesion

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell adhesion.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of cell polarity

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

label.value: establishment of tissue polarity

value.value: Coordinated organization of groups of cells in a tissue, such that they all orient to similar coordinates.

label.value: signal transduction

value.value: The cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell. Signal transduction begins with reception of a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a receptor or receptor activation by a stimulus such as light), or for signal transduction in the absence of ligand, signal-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. Signal transduction ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. regulation of transcription or regulation of a metabolic process. Signal transduction covers signaling from receptors located on the surface of the cell and signaling via molecules located within the cell. For signaling between cells, signal transduction is restricted to events at and within the receiving cell.

definition.value: Note that signal transduction is defined broadly to include a ligand interacting with a receptor, downstream signaling steps and a response being triggered. A change in form of the signal in every step is not necessary. Note that in many cases the end of this process is regulation of the initiation of transcription. Note that specific transcription factors may be annotated to this term, but core/general transcription machinery such as RNA polymerase should not.

label.value: cell surface receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor located on the cell surface. The pathway ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: enzyme-linked receptor protein signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell, where the receptor possesses catalytic activity or is closely associated with an enzyme such as a protein kinase, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: receptor guanylyl cyclase signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses guanylyl cyclase activity, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: cell surface receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses tyrosine kinase activity, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: activation of transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity

value.value: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label.value: signal complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a complex capable of relaying a signal within a cell.

label.value: epidermal growth factor receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a ligand to the tyrosine kinase receptor EGFR (ERBB1) on the surface of a cell. The pathway ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: epidermal growth factor catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of epidermal growth factor (EGF), following internalization of the receptor-bound ligand into the signal-receiving cell. Full breakdown of epidermal growth factor results in a ligand that is unable to bind and activate its receptor.

definition.value: This term describes the breakdown of epidermal growth factor within the cell, following internalization. For proteolysis events that result in the maturation of an epidermal growth factor receptor ligand, see 'epidermal growth factor receptor ligand maturation ; GO:'.

label.value: negative regulation of epidermal growth factor-activated receptor activity

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of EGF-activated receptor activity.

label.value: regulation of epidermal growth factor-activated receptor activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of EGF-activated receptor activity.

label.value: cell surface receptor protein serine/threonine kinase signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses serine/threonine kinase activity, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: transforming growth factor beta receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a transforming growth factor beta receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: transforming growth factor beta receptor complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a ligand-bound type II transforming growth factor beta (TGF-beta) receptor dimer with a type I TGF-beta receptor dimer, following ligand binding, to form a heterotetrameric TGF-beta receptor complex.

label.value: cell surface receptor protein tyrosine phosphatase signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses protein tyrosine phosphatase activity, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by a ligand binding to its receptor, in which the activated receptor promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha-subunit of an associated heterotrimeric G-protein complex. The GTP-bound activated alpha-G-protein then dissociates from the beta- and gamma-subunits to further transmit the signal within the cell. The pathway begins with receptor-ligand interaction, and ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process. The pathway can start from the plasma membrane, Golgi or nuclear membrane.

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway, coupled to cyclic nucleotide second messenger

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway in which the signal is transmitted via the activation or inhibition of a nucleotide cyclase activity and a subsequent change in the concentration of a cyclic nucleotide.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-modulating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway in which the signal is transmitted via the activation or inhibition of adenylyl cyclase activity and a subsequent change in the intracellular concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

definition.value: This term is intended to cover steps in a GPCR signaling pathway both upstream and downstream of adenylate-cyclase activity. For steps upstream of adenylate cyclase activity, consider instead annotating to 'regulation of adenylate cyclase activity involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway ; GO:0010578.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway in which the signal is transmitted via the activation of adenylyl cyclase activity which results in an increase in the intracellular concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP). This pathway is negatively regulated by phosphodiesterase, which cleaves cAMP and terminates the signaling.

definition.value: This term can be used to annotate ligands, receptors and G-proteins that lead to activation of adenylate cyclase activity within a signaling pathway.

label.value: activation of adenylate cyclase activity

value.value: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme adenylate cyclase.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating dopamine receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by dopamine binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating serotonin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by serotonin binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway in which the signal is transmitted via the inhibition of adenylyl cyclase activity and a subsequent decrease in the intracellular concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

definition.value: This term is intended to cover steps in a GPCR signaling pathway both upstream and downstream of adenylate-cyclase inhibition.

label.value: negative regulation of adenylate cyclase activity

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of adenylate cyclase activity.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting dopamine receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by dopamine binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled glutamate receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by glutamate binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by acetylcholine binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting serotonin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by serotonin binding to its receptor, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway coupled to cGMP nucleotide second messenger

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G protein-coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, followed by activation of guanylyl cyclase (GC) activity and a subsequent increase in the concentration of cyclic GMP (cGMP).

label.value: phospholipase C-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway in which the signal is transmitted via the activation of phospholipase C (PLC) and a subsequent increase in the intracellular concentration of inositol trisphosphate (IP3) and diacylglycerol (DAG). IP3 regulates the opening of calcium channels in intracellular calcium store, leading to the release of calcium into the cytosol. Calcium and DAG activate protein kinase C (PKC), which in turn activates downstream effectors.

label.value: positive regulation of cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: Any process that increases the concentration of calcium ions in the cytosol.

label.value: phospholipase C-activating G protein-coupled glutamate receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A phospholipase C-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by glutamate binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: phospholipase C-activating G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A phospholipase C-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by acetylcholine binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: phospholipase C-activating serotonin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A phospholipase C-activating receptor G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by serotonin binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: phospholipase C-activating tachykinin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A phospholipase C-activating receptor G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by tachykinin binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.
